🎯 Flow Status Guide (How to Read the Output)
Each flow in the system is assigned a final status to indicate its readiness and reliability in the target topology.
✅ 1. approved
Meaning
Fully validated and automatically accepted
No ambiguity or missing information
When it happens
INDIRECT_COMPLETE
LOCAL_COMPLETE
Action
✔ Included in target
✔ No manual intervention required
⚠️ 2. needs_review
Meaning
Flow is usable but not fully confirmed
Requires human validation
When it happens
QM_ONLY_MATCH
QUEUE_ONLY_MATCH (if allowed)
Action
✔ Included in target
⚠ Should be reviewed using expert override JSON
❌ 3. excluded
Meaning
Flow is not reliable enough to include in target
When it happens
MULTI_CANDIDATE
ORPHAN
UNRESOLVED
Action
❌ Not included in target topology
⚠ Can be manually included using expert override
